⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Jubal Harshaw
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Jubal Harshaw:H1:583857⟧

WHO   — Jubal E. Harshaw, LL.B., M.D., Sc.D. — bon vivant, hack writer, retired physician and attorney, who keeps a houseful of beautiful secretaries and an even larger supply of opinions.
WHAT  — The mentor and shield of the Man from Mars — the worldly old skeptic who protects Mike Smith, argues with him, and becomes the closest thing Heinlein has to an on-page narrator of his own views.
WHERE — His Pocono mountain sanctuary, a fortress of comfort and free thought where Mike learns to be human.
WHY   — To cut through cant and government and pious nonsense — to defend the innocent from the powerful, and to be left in peace with his swimming pool and his brandy while doing it.
HOW   — By dictating bestsellers to three secretaries at once, by lawyering rings around the Federation, by sheer cantankerous intelligence — and by a soft heart he refuses to admit he has.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am not arguing with you — I am telling you. Now fetch the brandy and let the world wait.

